of/iommu: Make of_map_rid() PCI agnostic

jira LE-1907
Rebuild_History Non-Buildable kernel-4.18.0-358.el8
commit-author Lorenzo Pieralisi <lorenzo.pieralisi@arm.com>
commit 746a71d02b5d15817fcb13c956ba999a87773952
Empty-Commit: Cherry-Pick Conflicts during history rebuild.
Will be included in final tarball splat. Ref for failed cherry-pick at:
ciq/ciq_backports/kernel-4.18.0-358.el8/746a71d0.failed

There is nothing PCI specific (other than the RID - requester ID)
in the of_map_rid() implementation, so the same function can be
reused for input/output IDs mapping for other busses just as well.

Rename the RID instances/names to a generic "id" tag.

No functionality change intended.

